sed "s/^X//" >'extensions/xv/man/man3/XvQueryEncodings.3X' <<'END_OF_FILE'
X.TH XvQueryEncodings
X.SH Name
XXvQueryEncodings \- return list of encodings for an adaptor
X.\"
X.SH Syntax
X.B #include <X11/extensions/Xvlib.h>
X.sp 1l
X\fBXvQueryEncodings(\fIdpy, port, p_num_encodings, pp_encoding_info)\fR
X.sp 1l
X\fBregister Display \fI*dpy\fR;
X.br
X\fBXvPortID \fIport\fR;
X.br
X\fBunsigned long \fI*p_num_encodings\fR;
X.br
X\fBXvEncodingInfo \fI**pp_encoding_info\fR;
X.\"
X.SH Arguments
X.IP \fI*dpy\fR 15
XSpecifies the display screen on which the
XXv Server is to accept requests from Xv clients.  If the
Xdisplay option is not specified, Xv uses the display screen
Xspecified by your DISPLAY environment variable.  The display
Xoption has the format hostname:number.  Using two colons
X(::) instead of one (:) indicates that DECnet is to be used
Xfor transport.
X.IP \fIport\fR 15
XSpecifies the port whose adaptor is to be queried for its
Xlist of encodings.
X.IP \fIp_num_encodings\fR 15
XA pointer to where the number of encodings supported
Xby the adaptor is written.
X.IP \fIpp_encoding_info\fR 15
XA pointer to where the list of returned
Xencoding information is returned.
XXvEncodingInfo has the following structure:
X.EX
X
X    typedef struct {
X      XvEncodingID encoding_id;
X      char *name;
X      unsigned long width;
X      unsigned long height;
X      XvRational rate;
X    } XvEncodingInfo;
X
X.EE
X.IP \fIencoding_id\fR 15
XSpecifies the encoding-id of the encoding.  The encoding-id is used to
Xidentify an encoding when a port's encoding attribute is changed.
X.IP \fIname\fR 15
XA pointer to a formatted string that identifies the encoding.  The string
Xhas the format "\fItiming-signaltype\fR".  For example "ntsc-composite".
X.IP \fIwidth,height\fR 15
XThe width and height, in pixels, of the decoded video image.
X.IP \fIrate\fR 15
XThe field rate of the decoded video.
X.PP
XThe XvRational structure is used to specify a fractional number.
XIt has the following structure:
X.EX
X
X    typedef struct {
X      int numerator;
X      int denominator;
X    } XvRational;
X
X.EE
XThe \fInumerator\fP and \fIdenominator\fP fields specify the 
Xappropriate parts of a fractional number.
X.\"
X.SH Description
XXvQueryEncodings(3X) returns encoding information about an adaptor.  Each
Xencoding is described by the XvEncodingInfo structure described above.  The 
Xencodings are identified by an encoding-id, which can be used to set or get
Xthe encoding attribute of a port.
X.SH Examples
X.EX
XExample between .EX and .EE will show in monospace
X.EE
X.SH Returned Values
X.IP [Success] 8
XReturned if XvQueryEncodings(3X) completed successfully.
X.IP [XvBadExtension] 8
XReturned if the Xv extension is unavailable.
X.IP [XvBadAlloc] 8
XReturned if XvQueryEncodings(3X) failed to allocate memory to process
Xthe request.
X.SH Diagnostics
X.IP [XvBadPort] 8
XGenerated if the requested port does not exist.
X.\"
X.SH See Also
X.\"
XXvFreeEncodingInfo(3X)
X.br
END_OF_FILE
